divs: Sighting DetailsI was with my friends sitting in a park and i happened to look up and see this what i thought was a star, it was kinda hovering about but it looked really out of place so i watched it for about 2 minutes while it just hovered almost, it just looked like a fireball floating in the sky, no bigger then a star in the sky but orange, and what i could tell it was pulsating. It "floated" for a while and then it just shot off in one direction at a seriously fast speed, if i blinked i would've most definitely missed it, but i felt like i couldnt move so i kept watching it. Certainly one of the most weirdest things i've ever seen and that has happened to me.
trends: There have been no other sightings in Eastbourne

Summary: Bright orb in sky hovering then zipping away.
